<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1950,2012]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1950,1975]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. A species with thorax entirely yellow with only sutures in front of root of halter and about laterotergite blackish. Sct present. Cell bm+dm long. Abdomen with tergite 
<number box="[874,888,1987,2011]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="2.0">2</number>
blackish. Male terminalia with hypandrium and epandrium clear yellow, surstylus broadly pointed emerging beyond tip of epandrium and bearing strong setae apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
